				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				That firewall does nothing to prevent the situation I mentioned.  You can filter all you want after the fact.  By using a hotmail account, all the email harvesters can send their spam there, and my personal address remains relativly spam free.  This is VERY common practice and again, is not considered &quot;cowardly&quot;.  Oh, and it does not cost me a $30 a year subscription to do this.<BR>
Of course you dont even need a firewall to implement email filters.  There is no way to completely prevent spam.  There are ways to help cut down on and fight spam.  Not spreading your personal address around the web is one of them.
